Performance: 4
The requirements provide clear instructions on how the functions should behave and what inputs and outputs are expected. They accurately describe the functionality of the functions in the source code.

Explainability: 4
The requirements are well-explained and easy to follow. Each requirement is clearly stated and provides the necessary information to understand the behavior of the functions.

Calibration: 4
There are no logical inconsistencies or duplicated requirements in the document. Each requirement is unique and contributes to the overall functionality of the system.

Faithfulness: 3
Most of the requirements are directly related to the source code and describe the expected behavior of the functions. However, there are a few requirements that are more generalized, such as requirement 14 which mentions checking the INACTIVE DATE of the DRUG file, but does not specify how it should be checked.